canonical:
  title: 楚州刺史張雄將軍
  author: 崔致遠
  language: lzh
  text: 牒准詔云云見功必賞漢高祖之殊恩承制無疑鄧司空之故事前件官材標落落韻禀錚錚自假使符已揚政績理股肱之名郡登耳目之高官信義相從功名愈振佇擅外臺之寄宜昇大樹之資爾其益勵忠規仰銜成命用副劉弘之善擧無嗟李廣之難封事須准詔行墨勑轉授右武衛將軍
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 楚州刺史張雄將軍
  author: 崔致遠
  language: lzh
  text: 牒准詔云云。見功必賞。漢高祖之殊恩。承制無疑。鄧司空之故事。前件官。材標落落。韻禀錚錚。自假使符。已揚政績。理股肱之名郡。登耳目之高官。信義相從。功名愈振。佇擅外臺之寄。宜昇大樹之資。爾其益勵忠規。仰銜成命。用副劉弘之善擧。無嗟李廣之難封。事須准詔行墨勑。轉授右武衛將軍。
korean:
  title: 초주 자사 장웅 장군
  author: 최치원
  language: kor
  text: 조칙(詔勅)에 의거해서 보면, 공이 있게 되면, 반드시 상주는 것은 한(漢)나라 고조(高祖)의 특수한 은전이요, 임금의 말씀을 받들어 의심없이 하였음은 등사공(鄧司空)이 한 일이다. 전건관(前件官)은 재표(材標)가 낙락하고 운품(韻稟)이 쟁쟁하다. 자사로 있을 때부터 이미 정적(政績)을 날려서, 고굉(股肱)같이 이름난 고을을 다스렸고, 임금의 이목이 될만한 높은 벼슬에 올라서, 신의가 서로 따르고, 공명이 더욱 떨치었다. 외대(外臺)에서 맡긴 일을 마음대로 하려면, 마땅히 대장의 계급에 올려야 하니, 그대는 더욱 충성스러운 계획을 격려하고 내린 명령을 잘 지켜, 유홍(劉弘)을 잘 천거한 것에 맞게 하고, 이광(李廣)처럼 봉후가 되기 어려운 한탄이 없게 하라. 일은 반드시 조서의 말씀에 의거하여 행할 것이며, 묵칙(墨勅)으로 우무위 장군(右武衛將軍)으로 전수한다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1090_010_0010&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Decree for Zhang Xiong, General and Prefect of Chuzhou
  author: Choi Chi-won
  language: eng
  text: 'By imperial decree it is proclaimed: when merit is shown, reward must surely follow—such was the extraordinary grace of Han Gaozu, and such is the unwavering precedent set by Deng Sikong. This official bears marks of excellence resplendent and bright, possessed of resonance pure and clear. From his time as prefect, he has already made his administrative virtue shine forth. He has governed those regions of trust as skillfully as shoulder and arm, and risen to posts of honor where the ruler''s eyes and ears reach high. Loyalty and righteousness have walked hand in hand with him, and his reputation for achievement grows ever more radiant. Since he is to be entrusted with authority beyond the capital, he must be elevated to the rank befitting such trust. Therefore, redouble your loyal purpose and faithfully uphold this mandate, emulating the noble recommendations of Liu Hong, sparing yourself the lament of Li Guang who found advancement so difficult. Let all things be carried out according to this imperial word, and let it be known through imperial edict: he is hereby transferred and appointed Right General of the Wuwei Guard.'
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: 'Deng Sikong (鄧司空): A Han dynasty administrator known for his administrative virtue and ethical governance, cited here as a model precedent.'
  - key: ''
    value: 'Liu Hong (劉弘): A Han official celebrated for making wise and virtuous recommendations of talented individuals.'
  - key: ''
    value: 'Li Guang (李廣): A famous Han general whose many accomplishments were never rewarded with enfeoffment, a cautionary reference to injustice despite merit.'
